"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-06-23-Egypt-s-rising-cycling-team-keen-to-impress-at-Paris-2024-1uF1sOZeg8M-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Adel El Mahrouky  Copied  The rising cycling team of Egypt will be seeking to impress at the coming 2024 Summer Olympic Games in Paris after securing four out of the five slots reserved for Africa.  In recent years, the North African country has been investing heavily in the construction of a state-of-the-art cycling track and team and the rewards are now being seen with Egypt quickly rising into a force on the continent.  Since the team was inaugurated in 2021, Cairo has hosted a number of continental and international events giving local cyclists the exposure they needed to compete against the best.  \\\"In the World Junior category we are advancing significantly, our players are ranked from 5th to 9th and we are now the fifth best nation in the world in that age category,\\\" Egypt's coach Mohamed Ibrahim told CGTN. \\\"We are now the Arab Champions and the African Champions against fierce competition from South Africa which used to dominate the continent.\\\"  Shahd Saeed, 19, will make his Olympic debut in Paris, as the new African record holder for the 500-meter sprint racing event.  \\\"I am surprised to have qualified,\\\" Saeed said. \\\"I did not imagine that I would reach that far so fast. It's my dream to become an Olympic athlete. I will do my best to do well in the Paris Olympics. I hope to make my family and country proud\\\"  \\\"We were not far from the international level in cycling,\\\" Saeed's teammate Mahmoud Bakr said. \\\"Recently we have become capable of challenging top athletes. We are still gaining experience. Hopefully soon we could be standing on a global podium.\\\"  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR 